			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I mentioned this idea to a couple mages in my guild, and they thought it to be interesting.  As mages, we have no defense other than our pet and gate, which has been a problem for us for a while.  So far, no good ideas have come about.  I do not consider root/snare to be a good option.  Frankly, I don't EVER want to see us get those abilities.  Here's what I propose.
<br />

<br />
We all know how good of a rune we can cast on our pets is.  For those who don't have the spell, each level of rune absorbs a specific number of hits of damage with no cap on how much damage can be taken.  A hit for 1 damage and a hit for 3,000 damage count as equals.  This rune absorbs AE damage as well as melee damage.  What I propose is to give mages a rune exactly like this.  This is definitely a very powerful self rune to cast on one PC, but think of it this way.  To limit the power of this rune, we can give it a 3-4 minute recast time, as well as a hit of around 4-500 mana.
<br />

<br />
Some classes may scream about how overpowered this is, but think of it this way.  All other casters have good means of escape, whereas we don't.  With a long cast time, we can't chain it on ourselves to take advantage of anything, whereas other casters can (in mentioning this, I was once in an LDoN where the tank went LD, and the wizard tanked mobs by chain runing himself).  Most importantly, since we have NO means of limiting our aggro, if we pull aggro, we have a better chance at survival with a rune like this.  With LR5, I can many times survive one round of melee from a EP mob.  I can't survive 2, however.  With this type of rune, I could survive around 2 rounds, and the tank may be able to re-establish aggro in that amount of time, thus saving me from death.
<br />

<br />
Let me know what you think of this type of spell.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=221279" target="_blank" class="postlink">Jimbop</a>
<br />
65 Arch Convoker
<br />
<a href="http://www.eotdraiders.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eye of the Deceiver</a>
<br />
Vazaelle Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
