				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">So basically it boils down to. "I want a rune".
<br />
Sony makes it pretty clear, "Mage pet = Rune".
<br />

<br />
We aren't going to get a rune or root spell *ever*. 
<br />
I'll say it again.
<br />
We aren't going to get a rune or root spell *ever*. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
What we should ask for is ways to improve the concept of our pet being our protector. (pets zoning and being up after camp or LD return would pretty much alleviate it). Pets that automatically change targets instantly to the last mob that damaged the mage. That kind of thing. 
<br />

<br />
Don't kid yourself, my now "main" is a 65/170 wizard with epic. 800 HP rune is nice, but it lasts through about 1/3 a round vs a GoD mob. Yay! What you want is a rune even more powerful than that given to mages (could take 3 hits of any amount) and that's just a laughable imbalance.
<br />

<br />
No, I'd vote for "if pet is our defense, make it even more so." Not all of us just want "give me more" because that makes the game Zzzz. I wouldn't mind if the mage is a frail little pasty panzy as long as if my pet is a serious bad ass that "can" protect me.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
